  }, mdx("p", null, "In this section, we shall be looking briefly at Tchaikovsky\u2019s compositional methods, inspirations and motivations. Then we will dive into a long-overdue musical journey in which we\u2019ll look first at my own methods and how I relate the ideas and findings of this research to my own creative musical adaptations ."), mdx("p", null, "The journey will be divided into 5 stops: Prologue, Village, Forest, Ireland, and Epilogue. We will look at the breakdown of each ", mdx("i", null, "stop"), " first, after which the entire arrangement will be revealed ."), mdx("p", null, "Tchaikovsky often sneakily adds folk melody to some of his music. So to mirror that, fun easter eggs -- snippets of his other music (not the concerto), will pop up here and there as we listen, so keep an ear out!")), mdx("h1", null, "Baseline"), mdx("div", {
